iteratur -- tZwischen Zeugniszwang und Schweigegebot Literarische Erinnerungsarbeit bei Primo Levi und Peter Weiss0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  a  aApproaches to a history of European mentality in the modern age are derived here from the confrontation of thematically related works in German and Italian literature. The emphasis is on the following topics: the universal idea of Europe advanced in Romanticism and its replacement by national concepts, the corresponding forms taken by the historiography of national literature, the concepts of melancholy operative in the age of restoration, the specific national variations on the theme of decadence, the positions taken up by European conservatism and aestheticism, the comparison between Italian futurism and German expressionism, strategies for coming to terms with the First and Second World War, and literary memorialization of the holocaust.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aGerman literaturey19th centuryxHistory and criticismvCongresses. 0aGerman literaturey20th centuryxHistory and criticismvCongresses. 0aRomanticismzGermanyvCongresses. 0aRomanticismzItalyvCongresses. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / German.2bisacsh1 aBecker, Claudia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBurdorf, Dieter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDurzak, Manfred, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKemper, Dirk, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKemper, Dirk, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSanna, Simonetta, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aScimonello, Giovanni, econtributor.4ctb4h